How to play:
WASD for movement, LShift to sprint.

JKLU for different color grading filters and tints, J is Warm, K is Custom, L is Cool, and K is Cold. P to Disable textures (im most familiar with the jkluiop FGC hotkeys)

1,2 and 3 keys are for the different light setups. 1 is diffuse, 2 is ambient and 3 is specular(the least bugged in my opinion.

Updates:
LUT contribution lowered to allow better visibility

Documentation/Explanation:

Asset Log:
Night Skybox: Taken from the Unity asset store to serve for world reflection. It's also the reason why the walls are rather dark. 

Materials: For each of the shaders.

Scripts: Either to enable mechanics like the lighting and LUT Swaps or to enable certain features like the camera, movement, etc. Many scripts were dedicated to allowing dynamic objects like the moving walls, and the pickup idle animation (the teleport cube). Movement mechanics and camera mouse control were mostly developed by me with a few online references to fix certain bugs like camera rotation and slow movement acceleration. Shader and LUT swap code borrows from a guide to arrays in a Unity discussions forum. (originally was asking on renderer mesh swaps, adapted for current purpose)


Text: Final text for win con(it can technically be a victory screenâ€¦)

Textures and maps: Originally taken from a texture I made in Adobe substance designer for a 3d model. Applied the normal map for shaders and changed a bit to avoid stretched textures as much as possible. Completely my own work.


LUTs are changed with photoshop. Render texture to enable LUTs.

Shaders: 

Borrows quite a bit from Lectures and slides codes as well as links in the slides that lead to unity documentation as well as external slides. Lecture 4 and 5 as well as the labs were crucial in this regard. Some variables were left blank because utilizing them led to errors but not having it in the code broke the shader completely(most apparent in the lighting shaders).
All lighting shaders were combined with the normal map URP shader code in lab 3, adapted with the help of online resources from forums, and then fitted on context to get results like below(Specular + normal mapping).

Shaders Pt 2: 
Attempted to Update shaders to include textures, normal maps and shadows. Texture sampling and stuff works just fine. Shadows do not work nearly as well.
Visual effects work fine, due to the texture I made in Substance 3D Designer, it can be used for both scrolling textures and stained glass just fine. The implementation is mostly based off class slides.
